Class 🍨 🐚Element⚪️

The 🍨 class represents an ordered mutable collection. Read more in the language reference.

Initializers

🐸

🔓 🐈 🐸

Creates an empty list.

🐧

🔓 🐈 🐧 capacity 🚂

Creates an empty list with the given initial capacity.

Methods

🐮

🔓 🐖 🐮 ➡️ 🍨🐚Element

Returns a shallow copy of this list.

🐻

🔓 🐖 🐻 item Element ➡️ ✨

Appends item to the end of the list in O(1).

🐽

🔓 🐖 🐽 index 🚂 ➡️ 🍬Element

Gets the item at index in O(1). If the index is invalid Nothingness is returned.

🐷

🔓 🐖 🐷 index 🚂 value Element ➡️ ✨

Sets value at index. If index is bigger than the capacity of the list, the list is resized to a capacity of index + 1. Complexity: O(1).

🐨

🔓 🐖 🐨 index 🚂 ➡️ 👌

Removes the item at index and shifts all following items to the left in O(count - index).

Returns 👍 unless the index is out of range.

🐵

🔓 🐖 🐵 index 🚂 item Element ➡️ ✨

Inserts the given values before the element with the given index.

All items beginning from index are shifted to the right and item is then inserted at index. Complexity: O(count - index).

🐔

🔓 🐖 🐔 ➡️ 🚂

Returns the number of items in the list.

🐼

🔓 🐖 🐼 ➡️ 🍬Element

Removes the last item from the list and returns it in O(1). If the list is empty ✨ is returned.

🐗

🔓 🐖 🐗 ➡️ ✨

Removes all elements from the list but keeps the list’s capacity.

This can be much more efficient than using a new list. Complexity: O(count).

🐴

🔓 🐖 🐴 capacity 🚂 ➡️ ✨

Ensures that the list is large enoguh to store at least capacity elements.

You should use this method if you plan to heavily use 🐷 with large indices in order to avoid automatic, useless allocations.

Complexity: O(1).

🦁

🔓 🐖 🦁 comparator 🍇ElementElement➡️🚂🍉 ➡️ ✨

Sorts this array in place using the quick sort algorithm.

comparator must return an integer less than, equal to, or greater than 0, if the first argument is considered respectively less than, equal to, or greater than the second.

🐹

🔓 🐖 🐹 ➡️ ✨

Shuffles the list in place.

🐰

🔓 🐖 🐰 🐚A⚪️ callback 🍇Element➡️A🍉 ➡️ 🍨🐚A

Calls callback with each element in the list and appends the returned value to the end of a new list.

🐭

🔓 🐖 🐭 callback 🍇Element➡️👌🍉 ➡️ 🍨🐚Element

Returns a new array with all elements that pass the test implemented by callback.

🐯

🔓 🐖 🐯 callback 🍇Element➡️👌🍉 ➡️ 👌

Tests whether all elements in the array pass the test implemented by callback.

The method immdiately returns 👎 if callback returned 👎 for one element.

😛

🔓 🐖 😛 🐚A😛🐚Element other 🍨🐚A ➡️ 👌

Tests whether this array and other are equal.

🍡

🔓 🐖 🍡 ➡️ 🌳🐚Element
